Step 1: Understand what constitutes total expenses.

Total expenses typically include all paid expenses related to operations, such as:
- Administrative Expenses
- Sales Expenses
- Financial Expenses
- Depreciation
- Purchase costs
- Other operational costs

Unpaid expenses (e.g., some interest receivables, unpaid expenses) are generally not included until paid.
